b'[<p><i><b>UFC 25: Ultimate Japan 3</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on April 14, 2000 at the <a href="/wiki/Yoyogi_National_Gymnasium" title="Yoyogi National Gymnasium">Yoyogi National Gymnasium</a> in <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was the third UFC event to be held in Japan. \n</p>, <p>UFC 25 was headlined by a fight between <a href="/wiki/Tito_Ortiz" title="Tito Ortiz">Tito Ortiz</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wanderlei_Silva" title="Wanderlei Silva">Wanderlei Silva</a>, held to determine the new Light Heavyweight Champion following <a href="/wiki/Frank_Shamrock" title="Frank Shamrock">Frank Shamrock</a>\'s retirement from the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a>. \n</p>, <p>The Octagon announcer was local Sanshiro Matuyama instead of the regular <a href="/wiki/Bruce_Buffer" title="Bruce Buffer">Bruce Buffer</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event featured the first UFC appearance of future UFC Middleweight Champion <a href="/wiki/Murilo_Bustamante" title="Murilo Bustamante">Murilo Bustamante</a>, as well as future <a href="/wiki/Pride_Fighting_Championships" title="Pride Fighting Championships">PRIDE</a> fighter <a href="/wiki/Ikuhisa_Minowa" title="Ikuhisa Minowa">Ikuhisa Minowa</a>. \n</p>, <p>This event also contained an interview with John Perretti, the UFC matchmaker at the time.\n</p>, <p>UFC 25 was initially seen live on pay-per-view. <a href="/wiki/Spike_(company)" title="Spike (company)">Spike</a> published a DVD release of UFC 25 exclusively in Japan, with a wider video release occurring after UFC was purchased by <a href="/wiki/Zuffa" title="Zuffa">Zuffa</a> years later as part of a DVD collection covering events initially unreleased by SEG Sports due to their financial difficulties leading to the sale.\n</p>]'